mainmenu "Alp SDK portable-API conformance suite"

config TEST_ALP_CONFORMANCE_WDT_ARM
	bool "Run the watchdog positive-open (arming) conformance path"
	default y if ARCH_POSIX
	help
	  The WDT row's open(valid) case installs AND STARTS a real
	  1000 ms RESET_SOC watchdog wherever a watchdog device is
	  wired.  <alp/wdt.h> documents that many M-class watchdogs are
	  write-once-armed -- close() cannot stop them -- so on real
	  silicon the suite would reset the board mid-run.

	  Default y only on ARCH_POSIX (native_sim wires no watchdog
	  device, so nothing ever arms and CI keeps full row coverage);
	  default n on hardware so the suite is safe by default.  A
	  bench operator may opt in to verify the positive WDT path,
	  running the suite dead-last and expecting a possible reset on
	  one-shot watchdogs.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
